Generally, I am always content with my food from Red Oak. However, there have been (now) three separate occasions where I’ve been disappointed.  Boneless Chicken and Loaded Tots have been 🔥. So so so good. Last night I ordered the Pepper Jack Burger and aesthetically I was immediately disappointed. This here cost $16.00.  I don’t always mind the price, because I’ve ordered from here plenty—but the “frittes” style fries were dry and potentially overcooked, the burger had way too much aioli sauce and dismantled my burger with each bite. It was messy, dry and aesthetically not pleasing. For $16.00 I could’ve gotten a better burger at a bodega with a drink, and more. My entire Uber order came up to $30 — it definitely wasn’t worth it this time.  Kind of disappointed and don’t see myself ordering from here in the future.  Poorly executed.

Luckily his body fought through the pain, my body unfortunately did not. Yesterday I was throwing up, fever, body aches and many more symptoms  of food poisoning. Now this is thing that’s really upsets me aside from the food being horrible this is around the holidays. New Years Eve is today and I cannot even enjoy it because my body is still fighting this wonderful virus thanks to the food! I had to leave work early and call out today. Never ever again will I EVER order from this place again! Disgusting and unacceptable for a place to ever serve food like this to people.

The manager:boss or whatever he was started saying things like he tried his best to take care of us; He didn’t charge us for a new head for the hookah( um.... dude the grapefruit head you gave us was legit used!!! So of course we wouldn’t be charged) even the hookah guy that came out knew something was wrong. That’s why we weren’t charged.
